{"title_page": "Roman Yampolskiy", "text_new": "{{short description|Russian computer scientist}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| honorific_prefix =\n| name        =  Roman Yampolskiy\n| honorific_suffix =\n| native_name = \u0420\u043e\u043c\u0430\u043d \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u042f\u043c\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439\n| native_name_lang = Russian\n| image       =         <!--(filename only, i.e. without \"File:\" prefix)-->\n| image_size  = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = Roman V. Yampolskiy \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1979|08|13}}  <!--{{birth date |YYYY|MM|DD}}-->\n| birth_place = [[Latvian SSR]] \n| death_date  =         <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)-->\n| death_place = \n| death_cause = \n| resting_place = \n| resting_place_coordinates =  <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}-->\n| other_names = \n| residence   = \n| citizenship = \n| nationality = Russian\n| fields      = [[Computer science]]\n| workplaces  = [[University of Louisville]]<br>[[Speed School of Engineering]]\n| patrons     = \n| education   = \n| alma_mater  = [[University at Buffalo]]\n| thesis_title =        <!--(or  | thesis1_title =  and  | thesis2_title = )-->\n| thesis_url  =         <!--(or  | thesis1_url  =   and  | thesis2_url  =  )-->\n| thesis_year =         <!--(or  | thesis1_year =   and  | thesis2_year =  )-->\n| doctoral_advisor =    <!--(or  | doctoral_advisors = )-->\n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students = \n| known_for   = \n| influences  = \n| influenced  = \n| awards      = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| spouse      =         <!--(or | spouses = )-->\n| partner     =         <!--(or | partners = )-->\n| children    = \n| signature   =         <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt = \n| website     =         <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}-->\n| footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''Roman Vladimirovich Yampolskiy''' ({{lang-ru|\u0420\u043e\u043c\u0430\u043d \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u042f\u043c\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439}}; born August 13, 1979) is a [[Russians|Russian]] [[computer scientist]] at the [[University of Louisville]], known for his work on behavioral [[biometrics]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inderscience.com/jhome.php?jcode=ijbm |title=International Journal of Biometrics (IJBM) - Inderscience Publishers |publisher=Inderscience.com |date= |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> [[Computer security|security]] of [[cyberworlds]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://biometrics.cse.msu.edu/Presentations/AnilJain_FaceRecognition_KU10.pdf|title=Automatic Face Recognition:State of the Art|publisher=Biometrics.cse.msu.edu|accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> and [[artificial intelligence]] safety.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.winterintelligence.org/oxford2012/agi-impacts/programme-committee/ |title=Programme Committee &#124; Winter Intelligence Conferences |publisher=Winterintelligence.org |date= |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> He holds a [[PhD]] from the [[University at Buffalo]] (2008).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cecs.louisville.edu/ry/ |title=Dr. Roman V. Yampolskiy, Computer Science, Speed School, University of Louisville, KY |publisher=Cecs.louisville.edu |date= |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> He is currently the director of Cyber Security Laboratory in the department of Computer Engineering and Computer Science at the [[Speed School of Engineering]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cecs.louisville.edu/security/ |title=Cyber-Security Lab &#124; University of Louisville |publisher=Cecs.louisville.edu |date= |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref>\n\nYampolskiy is an author of some 100 publications,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=0_Rq68cAAAAJ&hl=en |title=Roman V. Yampolskiy - Google Scholar Citations |date= |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> including numerous books.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&field-keywords=roman+yampolskiy |title=roman yampolskiy |date= |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> His work is frequently profiled in popular media, such as: the [[BBC]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-14277728 |title=BBC News - Virtual people to get ID checks |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2011-07-29 |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> [[MSNBC]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/46590591 |title=Control AI before it controls us, expert says - Technology & science - Innovation &#124; NBC News |publisher=NBC News |date=2012-01-03 |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> [[Yahoo]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Hsu |first=Jeremy |url=https://news.yahoo.com/humanity-must-jail-dangerous-ai-avoid-doom-expert-171005535.html |title=Humanity Must 'Jail' Dangerous AI to Avoid Doom, Expert Says - Yahoo! News |publisher=News.yahoo.com |date=2012-03-01 |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> ''[[New Scientist]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg21428705.900-silicon-sirens-the-naughty-bots-out-to-seduce-you.html?full=true|title=Silicon sirens: The naughty bots out to seduce you|publisher=Newscientist.com|accessdate=2012-09-25\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livescience.com/15432-virtual-sleuths-unmask-online-villains.html |title=Virtual Sleuths to Unmask Online Villains &#124; Biometrics Uncover Online Identities in Virtual Worlds |publisher=LiveScience |date=2011-08-05 |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> [[Alex Jones (radio host)|Alex Jones]] Radio show<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2YygKQh74Rg |title=Skynet Rising: The AI Threat to Humanity's Existence with Dr. Roman V. Yampolskiy |publisher=YouTube |date=2012-03-13 |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref> and many others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cecs.louisville.edu/ry/media.htm |title=Dr. Roman V. Yampolskiy, Computer Science, Speed School, University of Louisville, KY |publisher=Cecs.louisville.edu |date= |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref>\n\n==AI safety==\nYampolskiy has warned of the possibility of [[existential risk from advanced artificial intelligence]], and has advocated research into \"boxing\" artificial intelligence.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hsu|first1=Jeremy|title=Control dangerous AI before it controls us, one expert says|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/46590591/ns/technology_and_science-innovation|accessdate=28 January 2016|work=[[NBC News]]|date=1 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Intellectology==\nIn 2015, Yampolskiy launched '''intellectology''', a new field of study founded to analyze the forms and limits of intelligence.<ref name=Yampolskiy2015>{{cite book|last= Yampolskiy |first=Roman V.|title= Artificial Superintelligence: a Futuristic Approach |year=2015|publisher= Chapman and Hall/CRC Press (Taylor & Francis Group)|isbn=978-1482234435}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.technicallysentient.com/blog/2015/9/11/intellectology-and-other-ideas-a-review-of-artificial-superintelligence |title=Intellectology and Other Ideas: A Review of Artificial Superintelligence |publisher=Technically Sentient |date=2015-09-20 |accessdate=2016-11-22 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807183217/http://www.technicallysentient.com/blog/2015/9/11/intellectology-and-other-ideas-a-review-of-artificial-superintelligence |archivedate=2016-08-07 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.singularityweblog.com/roman-yampolskiy-on-artificial-superintelligence/ |title= Roman Yampolskiy on Artificial Superintelligence |publisher= Singularity Weblog |date=2015-09-07 |accessdate=2016-11-22}}</ref>  Yampolskiy considers AI to be a sub-field of this.<ref name=Yampolskiy2015/> An example of Yampolskiy's intellectology work is an attempt to determine the relation between various types of minds and the accessible [[fun]] space, i.e. the space of non-boring activities.<ref>{{cite conference |last1= Ziesche |first1= Soenke |last2= Yampolskiy |first2= Roman V. |title= Artificial Fun: Mapping Minds to the Space of Fun |book-title=3rd Annual Global Online Conference on Information and Computer Technology (GOCICT16). Louisville, KY, USA. November 16\u201318, 2016 |date=2016 |arxiv= 1606.07092 }}</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* ''Artificial Superintelligence: a Futuristic Approach. Chapman and Hall/CRC Press (Taylor & Francis Group), 2015'', {{ISBN|978-1482234435}}.\n* ''Game Strategy: a Novel Behavioral Biometric. Independent University Press, 2009'', {{ISBN|0-578-03685-1}}\n* ''Computer Security: from Passwords to Behavioral Biometrics. New Academic Publishing, 2008'', {{ISBN|0-6152-1818-0}}\n* ''Feature Extraction Approaches for Optical Character Recognition. Briviba Scientific Press, 2007'', {{ISBN|0-6151-5511-1}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[AI box]]\n*[[AI-complete]]\n*[[Machine Intelligence Research Institute]]\n*[[Singularity University]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://cecs.louisville.edu/ry/ Roman Yampolskiy\u2019s Homepage].\n* [http://cecs.louisville.edu/security/ Cyber Security Lab at UofL].\n* [http://www.eeweb.com/spotlight/interview-with-dr.-roman-v.-yampolskiy Interview of Dr. Yampolskiy on EEweb].\n\n{{Existential risk from artificial intelligence}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yampolskiy, Roman}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Latvian scientists]]\n[[Category:Latvian computer scientists]]\n[[Category:Computer scientists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Latvian computer scientist}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| honorific_prefix =\n| name        =  Roman Yampolskiy\n| honorific_suffix =\n| native_name = \u0420\u043e\u043c\u0430\u043d \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u042f\u043c\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439\n| native_name_lang = Russian\n| image       =         <!--(filename only, i.e. without \"File:\" prefix)-->\n| image_size  = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = Roman V. Yampolskiy \n| birth_date  = {{b